    <bioghist id="aspace_912cc3c6567b5dd58cc2766693073eb9">
      <head>Administrative History</head>
      <p>After several years of planning, the Harrisonburg-Rockingham County Child Day Care Centers,
        Inc. opened in May 1971 at Asbury United Methodist Church in Harrisonburg, as a community
        effort to address a widely recognized community need. It was supported at first by donations
        from local organizations, then by United Way and federal funds, and operated centers in
        several localities. Parents were charged for day care according to their income. A Board of
        Directors, composed of members of the community, gave guidance in policy making and fund
        raising. By 1991, approximately 70 children were being cared for. A detailed history is
        included in the collection.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent id="aspace_00d15d278c65f17a133cf1e3f531c182">
      <head>Scope and Content</head>
      <p>This Harrisonburg-Rockingham County Child Day Care Centers, Inc. Records, 1969-1991,
        consists of the two boxes of administrative files of the Harrisonburg-Rockingham County
        Child Day Care Centers, Inc., one of the first day care facilities in the area. Materials
        include a detailed history of the center, by-laws, meeting minutes, budget information,
        correspondence, memoranda, and newsletters.</p>
    </scopecontent>
